-- Hungary Stocks: E-Star, CIG Pannonia Shares Move in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-04-19T15:19:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-19/hungary-stocks-gedeon-richter-e-star-shares-move-in-budapest.html
Hungary’s benchmark  BUX (BUX)  stock index
was little changed at 17,553.13 by the close in Budapest.  The following were among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  E-Star Alternativ Nyrt. (ESTAR)  , a Hungarian renewable
energy and heating company, fell to the lowest in almost three
years after starting a “restructuring plan” to address
accounting errors and boost liquidity. The shares dropped 4.2
percent to 2,325 forint, the lowest closing level since May
2009.  CIG Pannonia Eletbiztosito Nyrt., a Hungarian life insurer,
slumped after shareholders authorized the board to raise
capital. The shares dropped 3.9 percent to 391 forint.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
